Preconditions:
- The input array `arr` is not null.
- The length of the input array `arr` is greater than or equal to 3.
- The input array `arr` is guaranteed to be a mountain array.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer `i` such that `arr[0] < arr[1] < ... arr[i - 1] < arr[i] > arr[i + 1] > ... > arr[arr.length - 1]`.
- The returned integer `i` is within the range `0 < i < arr.length - 1`.